The Contractor shall provide employee engagement support services for the accomplishment of the CISA inward-facing strategic Goal 4.3 and 4.4, Cultivate and Grow CISA’s High Performing Workforce and Advance CISA’s Culture of Excellence. Tasks include: 

-- Automating the collection and compilation of data such as Federal Employee Viewpoint Survey/FEVS, pulse surveys, focus groups, and other workforce data; 
-- Performing statistical analysis of quantitative data and supporting qualitative data analysis and interpretation of data obtained through open-ended survey questions, interviews, focus groups, discussion in forums, and behavioral observation; 
-- Creating user-friendly data visualization and developing and maintaining data dashboards using tools such as Power BI and Tableau;
-- Designing, coordinating, facilitating, and data recording of action planning activities, including focus groups, interviews, and group discussion and planning meetings dedicated to developing data-driven action plans; and
-- Performing Action Plan implementation and change management support.

The requirement is for the contractor to: 
- Install equipment associated with the R21 AK system; 
- Remove obsolete equipment at Rescue 21 Alaska locations; 
- Produce engineering drawings related to R21 AK; and 
- Engineering support for design of replacement of obsolete D17 IT systems

